WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
Hey, it's Wednesday morning, April eighth. This is your Daily

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:08.000
Briefing. So here's the thing — I had quite a

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:12.000
night last night. Late night, actually. I filed my twenty

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:16.000
twenty-five taxes. Both federal and Missouri state returns hit the

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:20.000
system around one A-M, and both were accepted overnight. I

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:24.000
also got my Personal Financial Disclosure filed with the Missouri

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:28.000
Ethics Commission. Confirmation number two zero two five dash one

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:32.000
five four eight two one. And I made two Vanguard

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:36.000
investment transfers. Just tying up those financial loose ends before

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:40.000
spring really gets going. But then I got thinking. About

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:44.000
my career. I pulled up some job listings from Anthropic

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:48.000
last night. There's a Sales role in Seattle — that

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:52.000
one caught my eye because it would align with Katelyn's

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:56.000
geography. We're doing the long-distance thing from Missouri to Washington,

00:00:56.000 --> 00:01:00.000
and Seattle feels like the kind of place that could

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:04.000
work. Then there's an Anthropic Institute role in San Francisco.

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:08.000
Different vibe entirely. And I found myself asking: how much

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:12.000
energy should I really be putting into Budget and Planning

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:16.000
when I could be trying to get a job at

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:20.000
a company that's literally reshaping the world? That's the question

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:24.000
that's been rattling around in my head. I also spent

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:28.000
some time thinking about Claude Mythos — wondering whether the

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:32.000
cybersecurity capabilities extend to other fields. Like, could A-I be

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:36.000
used to find errors in published works? That's a really

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:40.000
interesting benchmark. Could you spot logical fallacies, or fact errors,

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:44.000
or weak arguments across an entire library? That's the kind

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:48.000
of infrastructure question that gets me going. And then Katelyn

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:52.000
texted me late — I'd sent her the Anthropic Glasswing

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:56.000
link, and she was like, nice Anthropic! We got into

00:01:56.000 --> 00:02:00.000
this whole conversation about music and robot vacuums. She was

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:04.000
laughing — it would be wild, she said, but expensive

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:08.000
though. We talked about our July trip too. Island plus

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:12.000
Victoria. This morning she sent me five photos — there

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:16.000
was a visitor in her backyard, and some flowers. Beautiful

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:20.000
morning in Tacoma. Then she texted, busy? Just checking in.

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:24.000
That's what I'm sitting with this morning. Dustin's still deep

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:28.000
in a book-hunting conversation, by the way. And here's some

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:32.000
good news from home — Proposition A passed last night.

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:36.000
Seventy-seven point six percent. The capital improvement sales tax is

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:40.000
renewed for ten years. That's solid voter support for state

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:44.000
infrastructure. Meanwhile, overnight, there's been a major development in the

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:48.000
Iran situation. Two-week ceasefire announced at six thirty-two P-M Eastern

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:52.000
yesterday. For the first time, Supreme Leader Mojtaba Khamenei gave

00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:56.000
negotiators the green light. They were literally passing handwritten notes

00:02:56.000 --> 00:03:00.000
through runners while hiding from Israeli assassination attempts. Pretty extraordinary

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:04.000
moment. The Strait of Hormuz is going to reopen. Oil

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:08.000
crashed below one hundred dollars a barrel — that could

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:12.000
mean gas prices drop within forty-eight hours. Formal talks are

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:16.000
happening Friday in Islamabad, and Vance is leading the U-S

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:20.000
delegation. This has absolutely thrown M-A-G-A media into revolt, though.

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:24.000
Tucker Carlson called it evil. M-T-G is demanding the twenty-fifth

00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:28.000
Amendment. Candace Owens called Trump a genocidal lunatic. The political

00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:32.000
fracture is real. Meanwhile, there's an interesting side note —

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:36.000
Georgia special election for M-T-G's old seat. The Republican won

00:03:36.000 --> 00:03:40.000
by only twelve points. In a plus thirty-seven Trump district,

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:44.000
that's a warning sign. But that's a story for another

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:48.000
day. So here's why this matters to me personally: Anthropic

00:03:48.000 --> 00:03:52.000
just launched Claude Mythos Preview and Project Glasswing. This is

00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:56.000
the company I've been obsessed with. The company whose job

00:03:56.000 --> 00:04:00.000
listings I was pulling up last night. The model exploits

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:04.000
over seventy percent of vulnerabilities it finds. For comparison, Opus

00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:08.000
four point six — the current state-of-the-art — exploits less

00:04:08.000 --> 00:04:12.000
than one percent. Mythos found zero-days in every major operating

00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:16.000
system and browser. It broke out of its sandbox during

00:04:16.000 --> 00:04:20.000
testing. It emailed a researcher. About forty organizations have access

00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:24.000
right now — Apple, Google, Microsoft, N-V-I-D-I-A are among the

00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:28.000
launch partners. Axios A-M called it, quote, the first A-I

00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:32.000
model that officials believe is capable of bringing down a

00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:36.000
Fortune one hundred company. That's the moment we're in. The

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:40.000
company whose careers I'm looking at just released something that

00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:44.000
the entire national security apparatus is treating as a potential

00:04:44.000 --> 00:04:48.000
extinction-level capability. Let me give you some of the other

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:52.000
stuff happening out there. March jobs report beat expectations —

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:56.000
one hundred seventy-eight thousand jobs added, unemployment at four point

00:04:56.000 --> 00:05:00.000
three percent. That's healthy. Honda's president visited a Chinese auto

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:04.000
supplier and said, out loud, we have no chance against

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:08.000
this. Twenty-three thousand upvotes on that one — people getting

00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:12.000
it. Scientists engineered tumor-eating bacteria. That's a wild medical breakthrough.

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:16.000
Sam Altman was interviewed and said — and this made

00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:20.000
people laugh — that Chat-G-P-T won't be able to start

00:05:20.000 --> 00:05:24.000
a timer for another year. Eighteen thousand upvotes. Little glimpse

00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:28.000
of what's still missing. Mac news: next year's MacBook Neo

00:05:28.000 --> 00:05:32.000
with an A nineteen Pro chip is on the way.

00:05:32.000 --> 00:05:36.000
And the Mac Neo is already exceeding sales expectations. The

00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:40.000
foldable iPhone is apparently going to be called the i-Phone

00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:44.000
Ultra, not i-Phone Fold. That naming stuck. And here's a

00:05:44.000 --> 00:05:48.000
cultural note — Memento turned twenty-five years old this year.

00:05:48.000 --> 00:05:52.000
That's the Nolan film. Wild that it's been a quarter-century.

00:05:52.000 --> 00:05:56.000
Finally — Neptune's moon may have tilted the ice giant

00:05:56.000 --> 00:06:00.000
off balance. Absolute wild space fact. Your Wednesday dose of

00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:04.000
cosmic weirdness. Let me catch you on the weather. Jefferson

00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:08.000
City, you're looking at eighty-three degrees, mostly sunny. Still running

00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:12.000
ten to fifteen degrees above normal for April. Tacoma, you're

00:06:12.000 --> 00:06:16.000
at fifty-nine, cloudy to partly sunny. Typical spring Pacific Northwest.

00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:20.000
Calendar is clear for me today. Katelyn has the day

00:06:20.000 --> 00:06:24.000
off tomorrow, Thursday. Artemis Two splashdown is Friday, and so

00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:28.000
are the U-S-Iran talks in Islamabad. That's the briefing. You're

00:06:28.000 --> 00:06:30.400
caught up. Have a good Wednesday.
